<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98372038533511></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98372038533511><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98372038533511>RE: Weapons Guide lvl 1-13</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98372038533511#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=9764><span id=Scholar>Quiick</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>69 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 4th 10:39 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.04]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2> I've been using a bloodforged hammer and I found 2 problems with it.<br><br> The 50 dly makes it so hard to skill up.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had to dump 30 skill points into 2hb because I got tired of wiffing and getting killed.  <br><br> Second, as a Shammy I'm a caster which means I'm going to be carrying something in my off hand to enhance magic.  That means 2 hand weapons are out.  Carrying a shield and using a good 1h weapon makes more sense.  Why waste practice points on a skill you're going to discard in the not too distant future.<br><br>  I am using a spear now and at lvl 8 I'm getting by nicely and piercing skill is coming up on it's own without using any practice points.  I'm going to sell the bloodforged hammer and buy a decent piercing and stay with that.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
